reviews.text: An all in one place for residences nearby and visitors alike, with stores like Mannings (comparable to a drug store in the States such as Walgreens or CVS), Market Place by Jason's (like an American grocery where you can purchase laundry detergent to fresh sushi platters to Lays potato chips and sweets like Lindt chocolates to blackcurrant gummies), shops to cater to phones and where you can purchase Wifi sim cards which gives 30 gigs for about $300HKD to shops for hair care products and ones to cut and stylize your hair. JHC has a veritable variety of household goods and organizing containers. There are several restaurants to choose from such as for sushi, fresh seafood, rice or noodle dishes, to Pizza Hut and McDonald's. There are several bakeries with delicious cakes, egg tarts, sweet breads, and other baked goods. There are several learning centers where students go after school to learn various subjects. My youngest is learning Mandarin with writing in traditional characters and her tutor pushes for success.

Used to be a nice retro shopping mall with stationery shops and movie rental shops etc... But its turned into a place for nearby rich people filled with expensive restaurants and cafes that arent worth it
Old stores, fast food restaurants like KFC that have been there for more than a decade have disappeared
Rejuvenated mall now boasts a clean, well organised wet market on ground level plus a new Marketplace (upmarket "Wellcome") supermarket as well as McDonalds, Pizza Hut and Yoshinoya eateries.
After renovation, it have many good restaurants, from Japanese to western.  It also has some new kind of shop, such as catch game shop.

Homantin Plaza is a housing estate shopping mall operated by Link.
Currently under renovation, right now it seems a bit sparse with few open businesses.  
Star Seafood is the main Chinese restaurant, Marketplace the supermarket.  
The renovation for the wet market downstairs has been completed, and it looks clean and tidy.  Perhaps too much so.
Seems like when the renovation is complete, should be worth checking out.

reviews.text:
價錢昂貴度:中
大部分餐廳環境十分好
有兩間夾娃店(Namco&...)、玩具店
補習社&琴行
有中價及優質貨品,食店多元化 ,超市賣中高貨品。
街市凍肉舖有好多高級食材，價錢公道
這裏有翠河餐廳，但食物麻麻地，貴過係半山壹號間翠河一D，個商場沒有特別，有D嘢貴，個商場算是貴租，現在都有鋪位未能租出!

result.name: 大快活

reviews.text: 大快活的出品普通因為太多何文田邨居民去所以感覺很嘈和有時聽到粗言穢語我多数去公開大學的大家樂因為大部份都是先生和學生所以你感覺很寧静和食物也比大快活好很多所以我多數過条馬路去大家樂另外房署的職員餐廳食物出品一流價錢平宜又没有加一小費所以何文田明星酒楼向領展投訴說给他搶了生意所以2018年10月耍開會員咭明星一碟生炒骨要88元加一共97元房署53元免加一比明星大碟夾好吃明星要12元一位茶房署4元一位我是精明消費者我一定去房署

分量無標準
貴價嘅魚柳早餐，魚柳一小塊
粥麵早餐，麵份量少
拾枱大姐只拾餐盤，枱上茶, 汁不清理。不只是一次，是連續拾同一張枱的現像，行過而唔理。令人在餐厅内食得不舒服。
Comments  : Poor
可以一喫，冇驚喜。
無去過,最憎個代言人...
一句講曬 食物普通係啲經理衰啫
